Changes since V3-1

by AWE:

TCC:

1) support new guide config names (P1, P1-P2, P2-OI etc)

2) automatically configure wfs filter and fieldstop when slewing

3) move filter and fieldstop controls to the A&G screen

4) support OIWFS blending in Guide Loops (graphical display)

5) clean up and reorganize A&G screen

6) incorporate AO+M2 functionality into main loop enable command

7) move detailed AO commands to a seperate GAOS screen

8) disable new blending options in GS

Changes since V3-2  (by AWE)

1) Change all remaining references to Altair to be GAOS or AOWFS in
   order to support different AO systems in GN and GS

2) Fully integrate GAOS into the Guide Loop and aquisition and guide screens

3) Additional control loops, sequencing and underlying xml code are added
   to support LGS mode.

4) Redesigned the Guide Loop screen to make it easier to read and use

5) Reset in HAndset opens loops

6) Selecting science Fold position Sky>Instrument opens loops

7) MidIR defaults implemented (sequence closed loop and target to mount filter)

8) Implement/Fix Gaos Park for both NGS and LGS modes

9) Improve sequencing when closing the loop using GAOS (Check for Idle before continuing)

10) Added button locks on the System Control screen to prevent accidental parking or indexing of subsystems

Only in V3-3lgsdev (developed during lgs commissioning)

11) Added monitoring of aoSettled to the A&G screen

12) Only close STRAP loop if aoSettled is true

13) implement reuse Gains in LgsMode.  Automatically configured and can be manually controlled from the GAOS subsystem screen

14) Added SFO guide Alarm

15) Implemented GAOS Unpark

Changes since V3-3 (by AWE)

1) The internal TCC useLwfs state (retrieved by [AO state useLwfs] now requires the external useLwfs to be ON and that the Adaptive Optics configuration is something other than "No AO" or "".  Additionally, applying an adaptive optics configuration now redraws the Guide Loop picture, as new options may be available.

2) Added timeouts when opening and closing loops in the Aquisition and Guiding screen.  

3) Added BUSY/IDLE functionality to enable/disable/reset implementation.  Prevent ew enable/disable/reset demand when busy.

4) Many AO imrovements/refinements including: usage of altair's reues gain flag, monitoring loop settled status, handset offsets when using LGS only open/close the NGs portion of the loops, turn of Cal Source lamps when configuring, auto setting of NCPA and flexure filenames.

5) Added support for probe offsetting (used by the new TCS version).

6) Added gacq offset support: Popup generated upon receipt of offset demand and, if accepted, apply offsets.

7) Added command locks to Index and Park columns in the System Control Screen.

8) Implemented GAOS unpark, updated GAOS park.

9) In TSD, changed seeing label to V rather than R.

10) In the Handsets, override the arrow key offset bindings when editting the custom offset amounts.

11) Specify a site specific path to find the skycalc executable in calparams.<site>  skycalc is used to determin whether Chile is on Daylight Savings Time.

New Features in V3-5 (by AWE)

TCC:

1) Automatically sequence switching between NGS and LGS when using Altair

2) Automatically configure STRAP and change flux mode if neccesary

3) added a pulldown menu to configure SFO exp time based on star magnitude

4) automatically configure STRAP exp time based on SFO

5) added slew option to check for laser collisions

6) Prevent slewing if the A&G Sequencer reports port 0 for an instrument

TSD:

1) rewrote the Science Fold inPosition and Parked logic to use inPosition, Parked and Busy flags.
   Previously this had depended on hardcoded mechanism positions.


New Features in V4-0 (by AWE)

TCC

1) This version has been modified to support the new releases of the TCS (V6-9 and newer).
   It supports non-siderial guide targets and configures a new "configForAO" record which replaces the AOFold in the TCs for determining if we are using AO or not.

2) There are improvements to the implementation of the STRAP sequencing.

3) There is now a "force" configuration option in the GAOS screen which allows the user o reapply the config even if the TCC thinks that Altair is already in the correct mode.

4) Added NICI support: - check that the NICI nd filter is set to block before slewing
                       - configure NICI magnitude before slewing
                       - configure pixel router for NICI

TSD:

1) Changed the color scheme for the WFS Probes.  Instead of using a Stipple to show that there is a probllem with the nod configuration, they now turn orange.  This is to make it easier to see if there is a problem at night at 14,000 feet :) See TCC-23 in JIRA


New Features in V4-1 (by AWE)

TCC

1) Additional NICI support: - configure, start and monitor NICI automatic ND filter selection
			    - Added NICI Guide Alarm
			    - disable NICI specific options when not using NICI

2) Support for Altair NGS ND Filter ... check LWFS mode and control NGS or LGS ND filters appropriately

3) Fix small bug from V4-0 ... namedTarget Moon is now supported


