Branch V4-3-1nici

TCC
1) ca_config/pwfs2.ca: Created. It contains channel access definitions for controling PWFS2 (needed for auto-setting P2 gains for NICI).
2) ca_config/tcc.ca: Included pwfs2.ca
3) lib/CalParam.itcl (class CalParam): added variables for holding P2 gains (tip, tilt, focus). Each one is an array indexed by the instrument name.
4) lib/CalParam.itcl (CalParam::constructor): Added default values for tip, tilt and focus gains.
5) lib/CalParam.itcl (CalParam::p2m2TipGain, CalParam::p2m2TiltGain, CalParam::p2m2FocusGain): Created these methods for accessing the gains with the instrument name.
6) tcclib/TcsConfigControl.itk (TcsConfigControl::apply): Added auto set of P2 gains, depending on the instrument.
7) calparams.CP: added values for NICI P2 gains and defaults gains.

20080527 Javier Luhrs
TCC
1) ca_config/pwfs1.ca: Created. It contains channel access definitions for controling PWFS1 (needed for auto-setting P1 gains for NICI).
2) ca_config/tcc.ca: Included pwfs1.ca
3) lib/CalParam.itcl (class CalParam): added variables for holding P1 gains (tip, tilt, focus). Those, and the ones for P2, now are indexed by the instrument name and guiding mode.
4) lib/CalParam.itcl (CalParam::p2m2TipGain, CalParam::p2m2TiltGain, CalParam::p2m2FocusGain): Added the guiding mode as parameter.
5) lib/CalParam.itcl (CalParam::p1m2TipGain, CalParam::p1m2TiltGain, CalParam::p1m2FocusGain): Created these methods for accessing the P1 gains.
6) tcclib/TcsConfigControl.itk (TcsConfigControl::apply): Added auto set of P1 gains, depending on the instrument and guiding mode. Changed the implementation for P2 to add the guiding mode.
7) tcclib/TcsConfigControl.itk Changed previous implementation for autosetting default M2 gains for P1/P2. Now it issues default command to P1/P2.
8) calparams.CP: added values for NICI P1 gains.


