V4-7
20081103 AWE
Altair/LGS Improvements for the TCC
- FLENS control now goes through the TCS rather than directly to Altair
- When a GAOS "No AO" config is applied, LGS Zoom tracking is stopped
- When setting useLwfs mode, check UStage and LGSZoom to determine whether the mode needs to be reapplied
- When an error occurs changing NGS/LGS modes, Force Config is automatically turned on. The next slew/GAOS Apply will automatically force the useLwfs mode apply and clear the Force Config switch. Any manual selection of "Force Config" will clear the "Force" flag after it is applied.
- Changed GAOS Park implementation:
          o No longer puts Altair into NGS mode.
          o Stops Gimbal(wfspos) and FSM tracking
          o Stops LGS Zoom tracking.
	  o shut down STRAP
          o Park mechanisms
- When setting useLwfs mode to LGS, check if the STRAP IRIS is open, if not propt user with the option to open it.
