20090323 PG
Fixed proper motion problems as described in Pat Wallace's document
"Gemini South Pointing Studies, October/November 2008", section 4:
- Made sure that the object coordinates use spaces to separate the fields
and before calling the SLALIB routines.
- Comment were added to justify the afct that the code should not used a
cos(delta) factor.
- Removed old code to test the effect of adding a cos(delta) factor. It was
commented out anyway.
- Used a fixed value for the right ascention (PI) because the result is
independent of this number. The 43200s range normalization was eliminated
since it's no longer needed.
